      <event id="10989">
        <start>16:30</start>
        <duration>00:45</duration>
        <room>M.misc</room>
        <slug>kubernetes_layered_governance</slug>
        <title>Layered Governance for your Infrastructure with Kubernetes, OPA, and Terraform</title>
        <subtitle/>
        <track>Miscellaneous</track>
        <type>maintrack</type>
        <language/>
        <abstract>&lt;p&gt;When writing policy as code, we aim to implement the best practices in our work, but we might not always know how to iterate on policies, nor how to make them transparent to the teams we work with.
The best way to enforce policy is to make it easy and to incorporate these practices into an automated pipeline that will make for efficient workflows and by making all policies visible to end-users. We will demonstrate using the Open Policy Agent, Terraform, and Flux in a declarative fashion.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
        <description></description>
