        <abstract>&lt;p&gt;Enclave technologies such as SGX generally have a relatively high context-switching cost.
This is particularly noticeable when doing (network) I/O.
In this talk we'll present the first non-LibOS implementation of an asynchronous I/O model for SGX.
This gives you a language-native async I/O programming experience in Rust, outperforming any other way to build SGX network services.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
