        <abstract>&lt;p&gt;Open-source software is code that is designed to be publicly accessible. Open source has core principles that make it rely on collaboration between contributors and companies in order to achieve a common goal. To attain more collaborations, onboarding in most open source communities should be considered a priority.  Oftentimes, beginners who are new to open source projects develop cold feet a short while after joining a community because they are not properly onboarded into the community.  Onboarding plays a major role in the performance of and productivity of contributors. In this session, I would like to talk on:
- What is quality onboarding?
